      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can think of the escrow agent as a highly regulated, impartial custodian, much like a bank vault. They are legally bound to follow the terms of the purchase agreement precisely, so their primary job is to hold the funds safely until the closing documents are signed. While no system is perfect, the legal framework surrounding escrow is robust, and any mishandling would be a serious breach of fiduciary duty.",
